SENATE PROPOSAL OF AMENDMENT H.398
2025 Page 1 of 1
1 H.398
2 An act relating to the Vermont Economic Development Authority
3 The Senate proposes to the House to amend the bill as follows:
4 First: In Sec. 1, 10 V.S.A. chapter 12, in section 254, in the section
5 heading, by striking out the word “STATE” and inserting in lieu thereof
6 “STATE AUTHORITY”
7 Second: In Sec. 1, 10 V.S.A. chapter 12, in section 280gg, by striking out
8 subsection (a) in its entirety and inserting in lieu thereof a new subsection (a)
9 to read as follows:
10 (a)(1) There is established within the Authority the Vermont Disaster
11 Recovery Loan Fund, referred to in this subchapter as “the Fund,” the purpose
12 of which is to enable the Authority to provide loans and other forms of
13 financial assistance to businesses, including agricultural and forest product
14 enterprises, after disasters.
15 (2) The Authority shall consult with the Secretary of Commerce and
16 Community Development; the Secretary of Agriculture, Food and Markets;
17 and the Commissioner of Forests, Parks and Recreation in determining whether
18 funds shall be made available following a nondeclared disaster event impacting
19 areas of the State. A consultation shall not be required in the event of a
20 disaster declaration declared by the Governor or the President of the United
21 States.
